Sulphide Indole Motility (SIM) medium is a bacterial [[growth medium]] which tests for the ability to [[Redox|reduce]] sulfates, the ability to produce [[indole]]<nowiki/>s, and [[Bacterial motility|motility]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://faculty.lacitycollege.edu/hicksdr/SIMtest.htm|title=New Page 1|website=faculty.lacitycollege.edu|access-date=2016-12-07}}</ref> This combination of challenges in one mixture is convenient and commercially available in stab tubes. Inoculated [[Inoculation needle|needles]] are then punctured into the culture and incubated, if the culture becomes cloudy the bacteria were able to infiltrate the media and survive.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://microbeonline.com/tests-bacterial-motility-procedure-results/|title=Tests for Bacterial Motility: Procedure and Results - microbeonline|date=2015-10-19|newspaper=microbeonline|language=en-US|access-date=2016-12-07}}</ref> This method is particularly useful for pathogenic bacteria which are dangerous to handle on wet mount [[Microscope slide|slides]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://vlab.amrita.edu/?sub=3&brch=73&sim=697&cnt=1|title=Motility Test (Theory) : Microbiology Virtual Lab I : Biotechnology and Biomedical Engineering : Amrita Vishwa Vidyapeetham Virtual Lab|website=vlab.amrita.edu|access-date=2016-12-07}}</ref>

